quote.p:
—Both sides would conduct research, development and testing, which are
                        permitted by the ABM Treaty through
                        1992;

—Such discussions would last up to two years. At the end of two years,
                        either party would have an unfettered right to deploy advanced strategic
                        defenses;

—While both sides would continue to abide by the ABM Treaty, do not specify broad or narrow
                        as correct; both sides would agree to disagree on this during the
                        period;

(D) 3300, for warheads on its deployed 
                            ICBMs
                        ;

(C) 3000–3300, for nuclear warheads on its deployed 
                            ICBMs
                        ;

(D) 1800–2000, for nuclear warheads on its deployed 
                            SLBMs
                        ;
